  "texts": [
    "These three main components are essential to develop successful IPEs.",
    "It is insightful to build a comprehensive database for the composites and then take advantage of ML to design the polymer composite electrolytes tailored to the predetermined requirements.",
    "To construct a unique and well-curated database that includes critical features, it is essential to carefully select and balance the tradeoff between the complexity of polymer descriptors and the specificity of the database.",
    "A key aspect of this process involves the development and selection of appropriate encoding types for polymer materials.",
    "Encoding methods, such as sequencebased encoding (SMILES), molecular fingerprints, graph-based representations and 3D structural fingerprints are critical for transforming multidimensional polymer features as well as inorganic crystals into machine-readable formats suitable for ML algorithms as summarized in Fig. 3d."
  ]
}